<TITLE> Blast kills 10 civilians in southern Afghanistan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KANDAHAR, Afghanistan, Aug 24,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A roadside bomb killed 10 civilians in the southern province of Kandahar on Saturday, the provincial police chief said. The attack took place in the Shah Wali Kot district to the north of the city of Kandahar, police chief Matiullah told reporters
